    <div class="container">
        <div itemprop="articleBody"><p><img align="right" style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 10px; float: right; display: inline;" alt="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2010/09/24/1225928/839170-the-social-network.jpg" src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2010/09/24/1225928/839170-the-social-network.jpg">As a software developer, you need a headphone and music to get into the zone. If I have to explain what “the zone” is, you might consider skipping this blog. Mark Zuckerberg was in the zone in the movie <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1285016/" target="_blank">the social network</a>. </p><p>My current headphone is a on-ear Sony MDR-NC7 with active noise-cancelling. It was the cheapest noise-cancelling headphone and I wanted to check out if noise cancelling would work. So if you have a nice affordable suggestion for a new headphone (preferably with noise cancelling) please let me know in the comments below. </p><p>As a developer, you know how hard it can be. If you have an off day: </p><p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en"><p><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/developerproblems?src=hash">#developerproblems</a> <a href="http://t.co/Gp5xqXhW2P">pic.twitter.com/Gp5xqXhW2P</a></p>— Microsoft Developer (@msdevUK) <a href="https://twitter.com/msdevUK/statuses/486140329213825024">July 7, 2014</a></blockquote>
<script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p>So here is a list of Spotify playlists for coders. Please feel free to share your spotify coding playlist in the comments!</p><ol><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/joannabutler/playlist/5DWd75wM11HGHF2rBgikAQ" target="_blank">A soundtrack for coding, 9911 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/125937873/playlist/5SgJR30RfzR5hO21TsQhBp" target="_blank">Coding programming hacking slashing – tracks I listen to while writing code, 2672 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/dkoy/playlist/4z0LJicquXnvHsjXE6SP67" target="_blank">Chill coding musix, 2625 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/redconfetti/playlist/03bKMoeCxREu1jKjPvCXwD" target="_blank">Music for programming, 1500 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/joannabutler/playlist/7EwKT4Mej3PWRWJLx1gAiY" target="_blank">A soundtrack for coding: the 2am session, 1042 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/aerotwist/playlist/17wLfa5r1UqZUHbrxG3coP" target="_blank">Coding tracks, 808 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/kyleballard/playlist/2GI6wbTjS4M4QHN8PbsIr0" target="_blank">Coding music, 463 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/wavyx/playlist/24BTJyV5sW6sNUEc4U21Lh" target="_blank">Coding for hackers, 386 followers</a></li><li><a href="http://open.spotify.com/user/simoncolijn/playlist/3gqWhmcHKsxvCtwa7LUmjj" target="_blank">Development on the beat, 348 followers</a></li></ol><p>The “followers” data is from 21th of july 2014. I will try to keep this list up-to-date after each comment. Ow and please post a comment if you have a good affordable noise cancelling over-ear headphone tip!</p><p>Good luck coding/hacking/developing/programming!</p></div>
